20/09/2005
DUBROVNIK, Croatia -- The 3rd World Congress on Chemical and Biological Terrorism kicked off in the Adriatic town of Dubrovnik on Monday (19 September).
The event -- co-organised by the US Applied Science and Analysis agency and the Croatian Defence Ministry -- includes 250 experts from Europe and the United States.
Issues related to non-proliferation, disarmament and arms control are being discussed.
(Novi list - 20/09/05;
HINA - 19/09/05)
